    <exercise xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" id="fs-id1844231" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id3104476">   
 <para id="import-auto-id2678077">What is the <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext>emf</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>x</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"emf" rSub { size 8{x} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> of a cell being measured in a potentiometer, if the standard cellâ€™s emf is 12.0 V and the potentiometer balances for <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>x</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>000</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.15em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">Î©</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{R rSub { size 8{x} } =5 "." "000"  %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>500</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.15em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">Î©</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{R rSub { size 8{s} } =2 "." "500"  %OMEGA } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2588490">
